This paper is about domain adaptation for sequence labeling tasks, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a fine-grained knowledge fusion model, which involves modeling the domain relevance of individual target domain samples, and controlling the balance between learning from the target domain data and learning from the source domain model. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deal with similar topics such as transfer learning, multi-task learning, and domain adaptation.
